{"article_id":"G1Ltdx8To7SAvOvP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As rioters rushed through the streets of Baltimore ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"torching police vehicles ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"looting local stores ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"and attacking police officers and reporters alike ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"some intrepid leftists justified the activity .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Marc Lamont Hill stated on MSNBC ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"\" There shouldn ' t be calm tonight .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"there can be resistance to oppression ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"when resistance occurs ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"you can ' t circumscribe resistance. \"","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"He added","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"that the riots should be called \" uprisings .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"The city is not burning","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"because of those protesters .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"The city is burning","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"because the police killed Freddie Gray. \"","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Sally Kohn of CNN tweeted ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"\" Looting is a real shame .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"But FAR MORE shameful is pattern of police violence against black community !","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Perspective , people .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"# BaltimoreRising . \"","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"Baltimore ' s riots have prompted a state of emergency in the city , as well as the calling of the National Guard .","depth":4},{"id":24,"text":"But the riots should also demonstrate conclusively","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"that leftist myths about what drives race riots","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"are just that :","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"myths .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"It turns out that all the excuses","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"given for the riots in Ferguson","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"simply do not apply to the situation in Baltimore .","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"The \" White Police \" Myth .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"As rioters tore up Ferguson last year in the aftermath of the justifiable shooting of Michael Brown by Officer Darren Wilson ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"media members rushed to explain","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"that the disproportionate whiteness of the police force was to blame .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"Media outlet after media outlet after media outlet after media outlet blamed the unrest on the failure of the police department","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"to reflect the community .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"But as of 2010 , \" Half of the sworn command staff are minorities , \"","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"according to the Baltimore Sun .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"And in Baltimore County , 55 percent of new applicants to the police department are minority , a number","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"the police department has been attempting to boost .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Racially reflecting the community , in other words , doesn ' t seem to be helping .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"The \" Evil Police Chief \" Myth .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"In Ferguson , the media targeted as its chosen villain Chief Thomas Jackson ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"who is white .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"After the Department of Justice found","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"that the Ferguson Police Department had serious racial problems","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"thanks in part to its disproportionate whiteness ,","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"Jackson stepped down .","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"Media found Jackson particularly galling","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"because Jackson released footage","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"of Michael Brown","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"strong-arm robbing a convenience store minutes before his confrontation with Wilson .","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"It is difficult to blame the riots in Baltimore on similar circumstances .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"The police chief , Anthony Batts ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"who is black ,","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"said in February","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that crime should be addressed \" through social justice as a whole , \"","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"and added","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"that \" Leadership should be focused not just on crime-fighting ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"but tackling racism. \"","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"He then stated ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"\" When I go to Baltimore , on the East Coast ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"I ' m dealing with 1950s-level black-and-white racism . \"","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"The \" Evil Mayor \" Myth .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"As Ferguson burned ,","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"media focused in on Ferguson Mayor James Knowles , a white man .","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"They suggested","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"that Knowles didn ' t understand his own community","depth":17},{"id":69,"text":"thanks to his race ,","depth":17},{"id":70,"text":"exacerbating racial tensions .","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"He ' s currently at risk of recall .","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"The same is not true in Baltimore ,","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"where Mayor Stephanie Rawlings-Blake runs the show .","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"Rawlings-Blake ,","depth":17},{"id":75,"text":"who is black ,","depth":17},{"id":76,"text":"said a month ago ,","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"\" To this day ,","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"if I go out with a mixed crowd ,","depth":18},{"id":79,"text":"people are automatically suspicious ,","depth":18},{"id":80,"text":"questioning :","depth":18},{"id":81,"text":"' How do you know this person ? '","depth":18},{"id":82,"text":"We have a long way to go...","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"Baltimore , like many other cities , still faces the challenges of racism. \"","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"As the riots spun out of control ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"she infamously commented ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"\" It ' s a very delicate balancing act ,","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"because ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"while we tried to make sure","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"that they were protected from the cars and the other things","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"that were going on ,","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"we also gave those","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"who wished to destroy","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"space to do that as well. \"","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"That didn ' t stop the riots .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"The \" Disproportionate White Power Structure Myth. \"","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"The nation watched the recent local elections in Ferguson , Missouri , of the City Council with baited breath .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"That ' s because the media suggested","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that the power structure in Ferguson ,","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"being disproportionately white ,","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"had somehow contributed to shadowy racism within the city .","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"The Washington Post complained ,","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"\" while Ferguson is 67 percent black ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"five of the six council members and the mayor are all white. \"","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"Not so in Baltimore ,","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"where the nine of the 15 council members are black .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"The mayor is black .","depth":15},{"id":107,"text":"The police chief is black .","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"Baltimore burns anyway .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"The \" Not Enough Government \" Myth .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"In Ferguson , the media and governmental actors suggested","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"that lack of governmental intervention led to the riots .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"Education Secretary Arne Duncan wrote an open letter in December 2014","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"suggesting just that :","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"We should take away from Ferguson","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"that we need a conversation","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"to rebuild those relationships , throughout the country ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"and that need is urgent .","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"It needs to involve everyone","depth":16},{"id":119,"text":"- our young people , our parents , our schools , our faith communities , our government officials , and the police .","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"It needs to happen now .","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"Lack of government is not the problem in Baltimore .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"Every single member of the Baltimore City Council is a Democrat .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"All 15 of them .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"The mayor is a Democrat .","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"Baltimore has not had a Republican mayor since 1967 .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"The tax rates in Baltimore are astronomical ;","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"the city carries the fourth highest tax rate of any city in the nation .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"The poverty rate within the city is nearly 25 percent .","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"Households in Baltimore earn approximately 56 percent of the overall state average .","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"Crime rates , of course , are out of control .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Modern race riots do not occur","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"because of the supposed white superstructure or a legacy of governmental underservice .","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"They occur","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"because valueless rioters act in valueless ways .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Baltimore is evidence","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"that glossing over lack of values with leftist pabulum about social justice doesn ' t stop cities from burning .","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"Ben Shapiro is Senior Editor-At-Large of and author of the new book , The People vs. Barack Obama :","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"The Criminal Case Against The Obama Administration","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"( Threshold Editions , June 10 , 2014 ) .","depth":5},{"id":140,"text":"He is also Editor-in-Chief of TruthRevolt.org .","depth":3},{"id":141,"text":"Follow Ben Shapiro on Twitter @ benshapiro .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":283,"left":278,"right":282,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":278,"left":164,"right":277,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":164,"left":146,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":145,"left":0,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":1,"right":143,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":143,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":163,"left":158,"right":162,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":154,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":147,"right":151,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":7,"right":150,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":8,"right":149,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":9,"right":148,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":155,"right":156,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":161,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par